he guidelines can be <a href="http://www.tpecc.org/images/news/AIAA_2012_eng.doc" target="_blank">downloaded here</a> , please search for the keyword “Austronesian International Arts Award 2012” or check the website of Taitung County Government Bureau of Cultural Affairs (<a href="http://www.ccl.ttct.edu.tw/ch/index.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.ccl.ttct.edu.tw/ch/index.aspx</a>).', 'AUSTRONESIAN INTERNATIONAL ARTS AWARD 2012 CALL FOR ENTRIES', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '338-revision-2', '', '', '2012-08-15 21:21:14', '2012-08-16 01:21:14', '', 338, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=344', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(345, 1, '2012-06-25 21:29:54', '2012-06-26 01:29:54', 'Time: June 28 &amp; 29, 2012 at 8pm\r\nVenue: University Theatre, 222 York Street, New Haven, CT 06511\r\nTicket: $35 (regular), $45 (premium)\r\n<a href="http://artidea.org/event/2012/926">http://artidea.org/event/2012/926</a>\r\nTel: 203.562.5666 or 888.736.2663\r\n\r\nAs part of the International Festival of Arts &amp; Ideas in New Haven, Connecticut, the Taiwanese theater company Contemporary Legend Theater (CLT) will present two performances of their unique Peking opera adaptation of King Lear at the University Theatre. <em>King Lear</em> is a solo performance with three acts adapted from Shakespeare’s <em>King Lear</em>. In this solo performance, WU Hsing-Kuo, the Artistic Director of the company, plays ten roles - King Lear, Fool, Dog, Goneril, Regan, Cordelia, Earl of Gloucester, Edmund, Edgar, and Wu Hsing-kuo.\r\n\r\nPlease come and join us to enjoy CLT’s <em>King Lear</em>. Let’s see “how Shakespeare sings Peking Opera.”\r\n\r\n<a href="http://tpecc-ny.org/wp-content/uploads/King_Lear_eFlyer_Final.jpg"><img title="Peking1.2" src="http://tpecc-ny.org/wp-content/uploads/King_Lear_eFlyer_Final-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>', 'CONTEMPORARY LEGEND THEATRE OF TAIWAN PERFORMS KING LEAR', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'contemporary-legend-theatre-of-taiwan-performs-king-lear', '', '', '2012-08-15 22:08:53', '2012-08-16 02:08:53', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=345', 0, 'post', '', 0),
