(432, 1, '2012-08-16 22:45:16', '2012-08-17 02:45:16', 'The Dadun fine arts exhibition is an international exhibition annually held by Cultural Affairs Bureau, Taichung City Government. This exhibition aims to enhance cultural exchange at an international level, and to manifest the characteristics of Taichung City.\n\nThere are 11 entry categories of the exhibition— crafts, sculpture, digital art, photography, printmaking, water color painting, oil painting, glue color painting, seal engraving, calligraphy and ink wash painting. Deadline of submission is on 13th April, 2012.\n\nA joint exhibition and an award ceremony will be held to celebrate the achievements of the winners. For further information on the exhibition, please see <a href="http://eng.taichung.gov.tw/mp.aspx?mp=18" target="_blank">eng.taichung.gov.tw/mp.aspx?mp=18</a>\n\n<a href="http://www.tpecc.org/images/news/DaDunApp.doc" target="_blank">Click here to download entry form</a>\n<a href="http://www.tpecc.org/images/news/DaDunApp_eng.pdf" target="_blank">Click here to download general rules and regulations</a>', 'CALL FOR ENTRIES: THE 17TH DA DUN FINE ARTS EXHIBITION OF TAICHUNG CITY', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '428-revision', '', '', '2012-08-16 22:45:16', '2012-08-17 02:45:16', '', 428, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=432', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
