(474, 1, '2012-01-15 00:50:03', '2012-01-15 04:50:03', 'Toronto / Harbourfront Centre\r\nJan. 20th - 24th, 2012\r\nVancouver / Vancouver Art Gallery Plaza\r\nFeb. 1st - 5th, 2012\r\n\r\nStarted in 2009, LunarFest is Canada''s premier presenter of contemporary expression in Asian arts and culture. Built as a festival that celebrates one of the oldest traditions for many Asian cultures - Lunar New Year, LunarFest is also built on an important artistic element for many cultures - the lanterns.\r\n\r\nThe 2012 “Lantern Aquarium” in LunaeFest is the world''s first lantern aquarium features a collection of lantern works depicting the beauty of our ocean creatures by professional artists from Taiwan, including Hung, Hsin-Fu<em> (Paper FantaSea)</em>, Shyu, Ruey-Shiann <em>(One Kind of Behaviour)</em>, Pai, Jung-Cheng<em>(Coral Reef and other lanterns),</em> Tai-Yuan Puppet Theatre and thousands of school children, with the sponsorship from Council for Cultural Affairs (R.O.C.) and Taipei Cultural Center in New York.', '2012 LUNARFEST', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2012-lunarfest', '', '', '2012-08-17 00:53:14', '2012-08-17 04:53:14', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=474', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(475, 1, '2012-08-17 00:53:01', '2012-08-17 04:53:01', '', 'LunarFest', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'lunarfest', '', '', '2012-08-17 00:53:01', '2012-08-17 04:53:01', '', 474, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/wp-content/uploads/LunarFest.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(476, 1, '2012-08-17 00:51:05', '2012-08-17 04:51:05', 'Toronto / Harbourfront Centre\nJan. 20th - 24th, 2012\nVancouver / Vancouver Art Gallery Plaza\nFeb. 1st - 5th, 2012\n\nStarted in 2009, LunarFest is Canada''s premier presenter of contemporary expression in Asian arts and culture. Built as a festival that celebrates one of the oldest traditions for many Asian cultures - Lunar New Year, LunarFest is also built on an important artistic element for many cultures - the lanterns.\n\nThe 2012 “Lantern Aquarium” in LunaeFest is the world''s first lantern aquarium features a collection of lantern works depicting the beauty of our ocean creatures by professional artists from Taiwan, including Hung, Hsin-Fu<em> (Paper FantaSea)</em>, Shyu, Ruey-Shiann <em>(One Kind of Behaviour)</em>, Pai, Jung-Cheng<em>(Coral Reef and other lanterns),</em> Tai-Yuan Puppet Theatre and thousands of school children, with the sponsorship from Council for Cultural Affairs (R.O.C.) and Taipei Cultural Center in New York.', '2012 LUNARFEST', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '474-revision', '', '', '2012-08-17 00:51:05', '2012-08-17 04:51:05', '', 474, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=476', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(477, 1, '2012-01-17 01:03:55', '2012-01-17 05:03:55', 'January 20, 2012 at 7:45-8:45pm\r\nJanuary 21, 2012 at 2:00-3:00pm &amp; 5:00-6:00pm\r\nJanuary 22, 2012 at 2:00-3:00pm &amp; 5:00-6:00pm\r\nJanuary 23, 2012 at 12:00-1:00pm\r\nJanuary 24, 2012 at 12:00-1:00pm\r\nStudio Theatre / Harbourfront Centre\r\n235 Queens Quay West, Toronto, Ontario, Canada M5J 2G8\r\nTel: 416.973.4000#1\r\nWeb: <a href="http://www.harbourfrontcentre.com/" target="_blank">www.harbourfrontcentre.com</a>\r\n\r\nFebruary 1-3, 2012 at 1:00-2:00pm\r\nFebruary 4-5,2012 at 3:00-4:00pm\r\nVancouver Art Gallery Plaza Theatre\r\n750 Hornby Street, Vancouver, BC, V6Z 2H7\r\nTel: 604.263.9311\r\nWeb: <a href="http://www.vanartgallery.bc.ca/" target="_blank">www.vanartgallery.bc.ca</a>\r\n\r\nThe Taiyuan Puppet Theatre Company, invited by 2012 <strong>CIBC LunarFest</strong>, will perform<strong><em> </em>T</strong><strong>he Boy, the Shark and the Sea</strong> in Toronto’s Harbourfront Centre from January 20 to 24 and in Vancouver Art Gallery Plaza Theatre from February 1 to 5. There will be 12 free performances, 7 in Toronto and 5 in Vancouver. Please join us and enjoy the show with your family.\r\n\r\nThis production, which features lessons about our interactions with the natural environment, tells the story of a boy, his tarot-root-doppelganger, a friendly shark and the community around them. Audiences will have a chance to interact with the puppets and puppeteers after each performance.', 'TAIYUAN PUPPET THEATRE COMPANY — THE BOY, THE SHARK AND THE SEA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'taiyuan-puppet-theatre-company-the-boy-the-shark-and-the-sea', '', '', '2012-08-17 01:06:13', '2012-08-17 05:06:13', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=477', 0, 'post', '', 0),
