(554, 1, '2012-01-10 12:52:18', '2012-01-10 16:52:18', 'Toronto / Harbourfront Centre\r\nJan. 20th - 24th, 2012\r\nVancouver / Vancouver Art Gallery Plaza\r\nFeb. 1st - 5th, 2012\r\n\r\nStarted in 2009, LunarFest is Canada''s premier presenter of contemporary expression in Asian arts and culture. Being one of the top 10 Cultural Olympiad events chosen by Georgia Straight in Vancouver, LunarFest was one of the spotlights in Vancouver Downtown Core during the Olympic Games in 2010, And, LunarFest is debuting in Toronto Harbourfront Centre in 2012.\r\n\r\nBuilt as a festival that celebrates one of the oldest traditions for many Asian cultures - Lunar New Year, LunarFest aims to collaborate with many Asian communities and outreaches to other Canadians. Since the inception, LunarFest is also built on an important artistic element for many cultures - the lanterns.\r\n\r\nThe 2012 “Lantern Aquarium” in LunaeFest is the world''s first lantern aquarium features a collection of lantern works depicting the beauty of our ocean creatures by professional artists from Taiwan, including Hung, Hsin-Fu<em> (Paper FantaSea)</em> , Shyu, Ruey-Shiann <em>(One Kind of Behaviour)</em>, Pai, Jung-Cheng<em> (Coral Reef and other lanterns),</em> Tai-Yuan Puppet Theatre and thousands of school children, with the sponsorship from Council for Cultural Affairs (R.O.C.) and Taipei Cultural Center in New York.', '2012 LUNARFEST', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2012-lunarfest-2', '', '', '2012-08-17 12:52:47', '2012-08-17 16:52:47', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=554', 0, 'post', '', 0),
