(599, 1, '2004-06-17 16:36:15', '2004-06-17 20:36:15', '2004 US Tour\r\n\r\nThe JU PERCUSSION GROUP (JPG), the first professional percussion ensemble in Taiwan, was founded in 1986 by Tzong-Ching Ju.  All members from the Ju possess great skills in playing Western percussion instruments, traditional Chinese and other instruments of Asian music.\r\n\r\nThe JPG has a wide range of repertoire, standard western classics, arrangement of Taiwanese folk tunes and children songs. The Group is also devoted in commissioning of contemporary music. Highlights of their commission projects including "Stiucgeua" by James Wood with the Amadinda Percussion Group at the Budapest Spring Festival in 2002, "Les douze Lunes du serpent" with the Les Percussions de Strasbourg (France) in 2001 and among others. The Group has toured extensively in countries such as the United States, Japan, Korea, France, Sweden, Hungry, Germany, Canada, Australia, and Holland.\r\n\r\nThe JPG has released 15 highly acclaimed recordings and two of which were awarded the Golden Tripod Award, an equivalent to the Grammy''s in Taiwan.\r\n\r\n<strong>Program\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nBoston/ Wednesday, August 4th, 8:00 pm\r\nSanders Theater, Harvard University (Presented by Foundation for Chinese Performing Arts)\r\nTel: 781-259-8195\r\n\r\nDartmouth/ Saturday, August 7th, 8:00 pm\r\nSpaulding Auditorium, Hopkins Center, Dartmouth College\r\nE. Weelock Street, Hanover, NH 03755\r\nBox Office : 603-646-2422\r\nticket prices are: $22 ( $5 for Dartmouth students)\r\n\r\nNew York/ Tuesday, August 10th, 10:30 am\r\n(Children¡¦s Concert)\r\nTuesday, August 10th, 6:00 pm\r\nLincoln Center Out-of-Doors, Josie Robertson Plaza\r\n(Free Admission)\r\nTel: 212-875-5766\r\n\r\nHuntington/ Friday, August 13th, 8:30 pm\r\n39th Annual Huntington Arts Festival\r\nChapin Rainbow Stage\r\nPrime Avenue and Route 25A (Main Street)\r\nHeckscher Park, Huntington, NY', 'THE JU PERCUSSION GROUP', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-ju-perc