(621, 1, '2005-05-17 17:27:24', '2005-05-17 21:27:24', 'Contemporary Legend Theatre 2005 US Tour\r\n\r\n<strong>The Kingdom of Desire</strong> adapts William Shakespeare''s MacBeth into traditional Chinese Opera as the story develops in Warring States period. With magnificent costumes and brilliant choreography, Kingdom of Desire infuses the singing, movement, dialogue and martial arts of Chinese Opera with modern theatrical techniques and live music.\r\n\r\nCritics have acclaimed The Kingdom of Desire is perhaps the first Chinese Opera to attract truly international attention and made possible a new use of the Peking Opera form in our contemporary world.\r\n\r\nContemporary Legend Founder and Artistic Director Wu Hsing-Kuo plays General Au Shu-Chen (the MacBeth role) opposite Wei Hai-Ming as Lady Au (Lady MacBeth). The production has toured Britain, Japan, Hong Kong, South Korea, Germany, France and the Netherlands.\r\n\r\n<strong>Schedule</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>San Jose, CA</strong>\r\nDimension Performing Arts, Inc.\r\nSaturday, May 21st, 8pm and Sunday 22nd, 3:00 pm\r\nCalifornia Theatre, 345 South First Street, San Jose, CA 95113\r\nBox office: (408) 257-6555\r\nwww.dimensionperformingarts.com\r\n\r\n<strong>Davis, CA</strong>\r\nRobert and Margrit Mondavi Center for the Performing Arts\r\nThursday, May 26th, 8:00 pm\r\nMondavi Center, University of California, Davis, One Shields Ave. Davis, CA 95616\r\nBox Office: (530) 754-ARTS\r\nwww.MondaviArts.org\r\n\r\n<strong>Charleston, SC</strong>\r\nSpoleto Festival USA\r\nThursday, June 2nd and Friday, June 3rd, 8:00 pm\r\nGaillard Municipal Auditorium, Exhibition Hall 77 Calhoun Street, Charleston, SC 29401\r\nBox Office: (843) 579-3100\r\nwww.spoletousa.org\r\n\r\nFor further information, please contact Taipei Cultural Center at: (212) 697-6188; or www.tpecc.org', 'THE KINGDOM OF DESIRE', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-kingdom-of-desire', '', '', '2012-08-17 17:35:03', '2012-08-17 21:35:03', '', 0, 'http