(647, 1, '2012-08-17 20:47:29', '2012-08-18 00:47:29', 'Friday, December15th , 2006, 7:00pm\r\nTaipei Economic and Cultural Office in New York\r\n1 East 42nd Street, New York, NY 10017\r\n<strong>One of ACC Fall Concert Series</strong>\r\n\r\nAsian Artists &amp; Concerts, Inc.(AAC) was founded earlier this year to help young Asian and Asian-American musicians transition from years of musical training into professional careers by providing invaluable performance opportunities. Already, AAC has concluded an ambitious first spring season including three full orchestra concerts at the General Assembly of the United Nations, the Philippine Center''s Kalayaan Hall, and Alice Tully Hall at Lincoln Center; and four Solo and Chamber Music Concerts at the Sony Club, Ise Gallery, the Nippon Club and the Residence of Consul General of Japan.\r\n\r\nACC also provides its musicians with the invaluable experience of learning from distinguished Guest Artists in master classes and in performance. As an example, Yamada observes, "For ACC Orchestra members to play along side a modern master like pianist Walter Hautzig, as they will at our First Gala Concert in January, is a priceless opportunity."\r\n\r\nThese performances are made possible through generous support of the Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in New York.\r\n\r\n<strong>Program</strong>\r\n1. J. S. Bach "Concert for Oboe and Violin" in C minor, BWV 1060 Yamada\r\n2. W. A. Mozart "Piano Quintet" in E flat major, K. 452\r\n3. Victor Ewald Brass Quintet No.1, Op.5\r\n4. F. Mendelssohn "String Octet" in E flat major, Op.20', 'CHAMBER MUSIC CONCERT ONE OF ACC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision-3', '', '', '2012-08-17 20:47:29', '2012-08-18 00:47:29', '', 634, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=647', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
