(857, 1, '2007-05-19 00:00:17', '2007-05-19 04:00:17', 'JULY 19-28, ASIA SOCIETY, NY\r\n\r\nCome savor the best of Asian and Asian American cinemas at the Asian American International Film Festival (AAIFF), as we celebrate our BIG 3-0 in July! Take part in 8 days of festivities from July 19-28! We have put together an amazing line-up of programs: 25 new exciting features; more than 90 short films and music videos; Screenplay Reading; 72-Hour Film Shootout; Comics Writers panel; 70s theme party; and much much more!\r\n\r\nThe Taipei Cultural Center is proud to co-sponsor the New York premieres of two award-winning Taiwan films at the 30th AAIFF, DO OVER and ETERNAL SUMMER.\r\n\r\nSPECIAL DISCOUNT FOR TAIPEI CULTURAL CENTER MEMBERS AND AFFILIATES! Taipei Cultural Center members and affiliates enjoy special discount of $8 per ticket to the two programs. Use discount code TAECCO to order tickets online, by phone or in person. http://www.aaiff.org /Box-office: 212-327-9385\r\n\r\n<strong>DO OVER ( Yi Nian Zhi Chu )</strong>\r\nDir. Cheng Yu-Chieh\r\nTaiwan 2006 | 113min | Narrative\r\nSet over 24 hours on New Year''s Eve, DO OVER follows five characters who hold disparate jobs from a film PA to a mafia boss. But as their stories unfold, we see how seemingly disconnected lives intersect by way of fate and authorial forces. Superb cinematography and an unusual temporal structure create a palpable world in Taipei that''s full of mysteries and possibilities. Sunday July 22 | 11:30AM |\r\nhttp://www.aaiff.org/2007/films/film_detail.php?i=126\r\n\r\n<strong>ETERNAL SUMMER ( Sheng Xia Guang Nian )</strong>\r\nDir. Leste Chen\r\nTaiwan 2006 | 96min | Narrative\r\nChildhood friends Jonathan and Shane love each other with a passion, but is there something more to it? The second feature of rising Taiwanese filmmaker Leste Chan''s is a handsome, eloquent elegy to that possibility. It is rich of seasons, lived by a quirky pair of best friends and a girl who challenges their order. Sat July 28 | 2:30PM | http://www.aaiff.org/2007/films/film_detail.php?i=132\r\n\r\nThe 30th AAIFF runs July 19-28 at the Asia Society (725 Park Avenue at 70th Street). For more information and complete schedule, please go to http://www.aaiff.org\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'AAIFF CELEBRATES THE BIG 3-0!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'aaiff-celebrates-the-big-3-0', '', '', '2012-08-19 00:09:32', '2012-08-19 04:09:32', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=857', 0, 'post', '', 0),
