(916, 1, '2012-08-17 22:09:51', '2012-08-18 02:09:51', '<strong>SEPT. 1 THROUGH SEPT. 30 2006</strong>\r\n<strong>NATIONAL DR.SUN YAT-SEN MEMORIAL HALL TAIPEI, TAIWAN, THE REPUBLIC OF CHINA</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Purpose:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the exhibition is to promote mutual understanding and friendship amongst the younger generation of the world through the exchange of children''s art works.\r\n\r\n<strong>Organizers:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Association for Education through Art, Republic of China (Taiwan); and the Association of Formative Art Education for the Republic of China (Taiwan).\r\n\r\n<strong>Qualifications for participants:</strong>\r\n\r\nPrimary and elementary schoolchildren between the ages of 6-15 years old.\r\n\r\n<strong>Artwork requirements:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Mediums</strong>\r\n\r\nOil paintings, water color paintings, wood cut prints, pencil sketches, crayon drawings and pastel drawings\r\n\r\nSize: Within 55cm X 40cm\r\n\r\n<strong>Number of entries</strong>\r\n\r\nEach participating country may submit more than one entry. All entries must include the following information in English:\r\n\r\nFull name of the participant\r\nDate and place of birth\r\nSex and nationality\r\nName and address of the school or institution\r\n\r\nPlease attach all identification labels on the back of the artwork. All submitted artwork will not be returned.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deadline:</strong>\r\n\r\nEntries must reach the Association for Education through Art, the Republic of China no later than May 1, 2006.\r\n\r\n<strong>Exchange of artwork</strong>\r\n\r\nParticipants should submit a request if they would like to participate in the exchange of artwork with Chinese students.\r\n\r\n<strong>Committee of judges:</strong>\r\n\r\nChinese artists, educators, psychologists, and art educators in the Republic of China (Taiwan) will be invited to serve as judges on the committee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prizes:</strong>\r\n\r\nAccording to the recommendations of the Committee of Judges, certificates and medals will be presented to the selected participants whose works exhibit excellence.\r\n\r\n<strong>Address:</strong>\r\n\r\nAll communications and entries should be addressed to: The Association for Education through Art of the Republic of China (Taiwan), No.62 Long Jiang Rd., Taipei, Taiwan, The Republic of China (Taiwan).\r\n\r\nPlease make a list of the participants in the form supplied by the 37th World Children''s Art Exhibition and attach it to the participating works.\r\n\r\nFor research purposes on children''s art education worldwide, please provide a copy of your strategic plans for art lessons, teaching guides, art curricula or new methods of art education.', 'THE 37th WORLD SCHOOLCHILDREN''S ART EXHIBITION', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '677-revision-2', '', '', '2012-08-17 22:09:51', '2012-08-18 02:09:51', '', 677, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=916', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
