(1452, 1, '2012-08-24 12:11:42', '2012-08-24 16:11:42', 'Assembly Dance Theater\nChoreography by Kuei-Chuan Yang\n\nThe Assembly Dance Theatre was founded by the artistic director Kuei-Chuan Yang in1993. Ms. Yang has renovated her dance vocabulary via an "assembly" approach whether the dance vocabulary is a combination of west/east or old/new. Thus the Assembly Dance Theatre is characterized by a cornerstone composed of indigenous cultural philosophy and its idea to assemble outstanding choreographers to create the worldwide dance language. For the past 15 years, the ADT has presented 140 performances in Taiwan and foreign cities, such as New York and Edinburgh. Many acclaims come for their meaningful and excellent performances. The Village Voice (New York) said, "Kuei-Chuan Yang swept into the country with her Assembly Dance Theater of Taiwan, redefining our assumptions of "modern" …choreographer Yang, whose maneuvers are serene while daredevil-athletic, Eastern in a uniquely Western way."\n\n《Drop and Fall》 is a piece that specifies in using the diversified movements of drop and fall for transmitting interpersonal estrangement, and strengthens brutality of human nature of life.', 'DROP AND FALL', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1450-revision', '', '', '2012-08-24 12:11:42', '2012-08-24 16:11:42', '', 1450, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=1452', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1453, 1, '2010-06-01 12:15:38', '2010-06-01 16:15:38', 'Taipei Crossover Dance Company\r\nChoreography by Xiao-Xiong Zhang\r\n\r\n《 Asunder III》 explores the most basic human desires and the most precious things the soul can admit and contain. Choreographer Xiao-Xiong Zhang draws on his background as a photographer, utilizing his strong visual sense to create striking pieces in which the dancer becomes a ﬂowing statue. 《Asunder III》 showcases this “photographic＂ quality, and attempts to portray humanity´s eternal quest to achieve transcendence in the face of hardship. By clothing the dancer in black-and-white angel feathers, Zhang removes all emblems of time and era, creating a symbol of rebirth and of the escape from original sin.\r\n\r\nTaipei Crossover Dance Company was founded in 1994. Having witnessed the growth of Taiwan modern dance on the local and international stages, the company focuses on breaking the barriers around the world of dance, summoning artists from different fields in order to experiment with a more pluralistic kind of theatrical art. Every year, the company invites artists of different ﬁelds from the world to collaborate. They explore both the experimental spirit and sophisticated technical work in relation to performance, while moving beyond the boundaries and confines of dance. Through drama, music, literature, painting, installation art, costume design, music composition and multi-media, the company has established a distinct style of “musical dance theatre,＂ and is recognized as one of Asia''s most interesting and inventive\r\ndance companies.', 'ASUNDER III', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'asunder-iii', '', '', '2012-08-24 12:29:31', '2012-08-24 16:29:31', '', 0, 'http://tpecc-ny.org/?p=1453', 0, 'post', '', 0),
